result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin R. Loging was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property (Over $2500) [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(2)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant may petition the court for a restitution hearing within 30 days - hearing to be held within 60 days. If no hearing is requested, the court orders that restitution be entered in the amount of $3215.22. **On December 10, 2014 the court held a restitution hearing at which restitution was ordered in the amount of $3,215.22. **

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No contact with B.Thom unless allowed by supervising agent with written consent for contact from the victim.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

supervisions.notes: ***Per correspondence from DOC the Court amends the credit for time served to 95 days***

superMiscConds.notes: The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with B. Thom, unless specifically approved by the supervising agent.
Defendant is to complete an Anger Management Program as prescribed by the supervising agent.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Restitution reimposed in the amount of $3215.32 and is to be paid in increments of not less than $150.00 per month. Payments are to commence on the 1st day of the month, one full month removed upon release to Extended Supervision.

Costs reimpsed to the extent not previously paid.  Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.

Argument by SPD:  Argues for 4-6 mos Co Jail sentence - appropriate sentence based upon circumstances. The Court:  30 mos term of imprisonment - 1 yr IC/18 mos ES -  hopeful that 6 mos will be served within the prison system.  Eligible for CIP and SAP.  1 yr term of IC/18 mos ES restated.   Wants Def to be afforded counseling and treatment options with this sentence.  Conditions of ES:  Rest of $3215.32 in increments of no less than $150 per mo commencing on the 1st day of one full month removed from release to ES. AODA, Ab Sob, No Bars, no possession of any impairing substances unless prescribed by a physician; Complete Anger Management Program as prescribed by Supervising Agent, Court costs paid from up to 25% of earnings, Eligible for CIP and SAP.
